<h3>Asides</h3>

<p>Standard HTML5 <code>&lt;aside&gt;</code> elements are enhanced with a set of classes to flexibly align them relative to content. This approach procludes the need for a dedicated sidebar. The <code>&lt;aside&gt;</code> element is often used to wrap <code>&lt;figure&gt;</code> elements, but can equally wrap any tangential content.</p>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> These asides are only designed to work inside the default compressed content column, not the mdium or full-width variants.</p>

<pre><code>&lt;aside class="ALIGNMENT"&gt;
    ...
&lt;/aside&gt;
</code></pre>

<h4>Variants</h4>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Parallel-left</strong><br>
        Modifier class: <code>.parallel-left</code><br>
        This places the <code>&lt;aside&gt;</code> in the left 2 grid columns directly parallel to the content that it precedes. 
    </li>
    <li><strong>Parallel-right</strong><br>
        Modifier class: <code>.parallel-right</code><br>
        This places the <code>&lt;aside&gt;</code> in the right 2 grid columns directly parallel to the content that it precedes. 
